gujarati.context:
Here is the translation:

Lord Hari has stayed for many days, Lord Hari's people; 
To be celebrated on Ashtami night, joy is in abundance here.

Here is the translation:

That great hall was built, my mind was made; 
Those seated ones are not worth a mustard seed, beautiful face, very pretty, lovely.

Farya fulake game naath, anshe ashi shriphal laai hath;
Pache aavyo ashtmino dan, bahu gulal laaviyan jan.

The translated statement is:

I went to the village empty-handed, carrying nothing but flowers in my hand;
Later I came with eight days' worth of sweets and took it back home.

Here is the translation:

The king says to you, do what I say, and we will rule the kingdom; 
If he takes this, then he will take pleasure from it, but let him come back to the village.
